{
  "stem": "2581.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "No one wanted yet to believe that I'll never see him again, because he went-- you know, I with my father was deported to the Lodz Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My brother and my mother were sent someplace else.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, when they deported our town, they-- we expected it any day, but whenever it happens, it's still unexpected.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Whoever could run and walk, walk and run, was chased into the Catholic church.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had a two-year-old cousin.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we all live in our grandfather's house in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And our cou-- uncle also lived there and he had a two-year-old boy, which was his-- his name was the same as mine, Feiwel.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he was there for an appendix operation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he was laying in the yard on a lounge.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The parents never had a chance to take this child with them.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And during that time, we were told by people that were in town later on, helped to clean out the town from clothing and other stuff that would be sent out to the Lodz Ghetto and for other things more valuable were going-- going to the German-- that they have seen the child shot.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He had-- you know, they shot him in his head in the alley, a two-year-old child.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And the fact is that many years after being already in the United States, I have nightmares.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I woke up in  the middle of the night.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I used to scream [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Herneke, ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Herneke, ?] don't forget the children, because that was on my mind what I had seen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "During the deportation, that is when they killed my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She couldn't walk fast enough.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
